news.title: Over 6,000 slum residents in Chandigarh face demolition
news.para: A total of 10 teams have been constituted for the drive, for which 1,000 police personnel have been deployed to quell disruption from residents being evicted.

news.title: Sand prices increase by Rs 1,000 per unit in Tamil Nadu
news.para: The association had launched an indefinite strike on April 16, urging the govt to withdraw the newly imposed mineral-bearing land tax.

news.title: Noida authority threatens to cancel AOA registrations over sewage disposal into drains
news.para: The Authority has already set the wheels in motion, writing to the registrar's office in Meerut against a residential society and one institution.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC initiates the demolition of unauthorised building in Dongri
news.para: ​​​​Officials said more than 40 residential flats, apart from shops and godowns, were constructed on the six floors. Before carrying out the demolition, the civic body issued a notice to the builder

news.title: Greece PM unveils financial aid for house tenants
news.para: The country's primary surplus came in at 4.8% of economic output last year, or 11.4 billion euros ($13.11 billion), according to a first reading of 2021-2024 fiscal data released by the Greek statistics office on Tuesday.

news.title: More than 90% Smart Cities projects worth Rs 1.5 lakh crore completed: SBI
news.para: The findings also showed that almost 92% of the funds were utilised across 21 key states. Uttar Pradesh, Tamil Nadu, and Maharashtra topped the list, together accounting for nearly a third of the total expenditure.

news.title: Ambuja cements completes acquisition of Orient Cement
news.para: The acquisition, comprising 9.59 crore equity shares, was executed through two separate share purchase agreements (SPAs) signed in October 2024.

news.title: Delhi environment department imposes Rs 40 lakh fine on construction projects for dust pollution
news.para: Officials said show-cause notices have been issued to four construction sites, each facing a penalty of Rs 10 lakh.

news.title: Delhi Police to monitor under-construction buildings by deploying drones
news.para: A senior police officer said that they use drones from time to time for extra surveillance of sensitive areas, but they will also use drones to check if anyone is constructing their residential or commercial structure beyond the permissable limits.

news.title: Delhi: DDA urges Signature View Apartment residents to vacate flats as deadline passes
news.para: An e-tender for its demolition was issued on March 17, shortly after the authority released standard operating procedures for the residents and the Resident Welfare Association (RWA) to coordinate the evacuation.

news.title: ITC Hotels signs 14 Fortune Hotels, opens seven new properties in FY25
news.para: As of March 31, 2025, Fortune brand had a portfolio of 78 hotels comprising 56 operational hotels across India and Nepal with 22 hotels in pipeline, it added.

news.title: Mumbai, Delhi-NCR, and Bengaluru attract $16.5 billion equity investments in CY 2022-24: Report
news.para: Together, Mumbai, Delhi-NCR, and Bengaluru attracted around $16.5 billion, accounting for a cumulative 62% share during this period.

news.title: Cement demand may rise 6.5-7.5% in FY26: Crisil
news.para: Weak state government spending in the first half also slowed pace of project execution and a slow real estate market impacted urban housing.

news.title: Sumadhura Group to invest ₹250 crore to develop residential project in Bengaluru
news.para: Spread over 3.25 acres of land, this project is expected to generate a topline of ₹500 crore and will be ready for possession by December 2029.

news.title: Banks approach RBI after being directed to raise risk weights to 150%
news.para: Risk weights determine the capital that banks have to set aside to cover credit risk; a higher risk weight leads to more capital requirement for a loan.

news.title: NIT asserts compliance with HC directives in Gunthewari layout plot regularisation
news.para: NIT clarified that the open space requirements under the Maharashtra Regional and Town Planning (MRTP) Act were not applicable in this case, as the layout was regularised under the Gunthewari Act, 2001.

news.title: Land acquisition poses hurdle for infrastructure projects in Bengaluru
news.para: In a letter to chief minister Siddaramaiah Sunday, Manjunath urged the govt to drop the proposal to acquire 9,600 acres of land spread across 24 villages under the Byramangala and Kanchanahalli gram panchayats.

news.title: GMDA issues 72 notices for illegal constructions in Gurugram
news.para: The notices were issued in the view of two key stretches from Sohna Road to Mayfield Garden and another from Baani Square to Golf Course Extension often being choked with traffic due to rampant encroachment and poor access planning.

news.title: Responsibility of stopping illegal construction lies with civic bodies: Delhi government
news.para: The department said it had got to know that local bodies, land-owning agencies and revenue authorities were issuing directions to Delhi Police to stop unauthorised construction and removal of encroachments, etc.

news.title: Kerala government to proceed with Global City project in Ayyampuzha after Centre withdraws approval
news.para: "With Centre withdrawing from the project, state govt now faces additional responsibilities. This has raised concerns about whether the project can be executed profitably.
